The reason basically comes down to "taking an n-th root" not a priori being a well-defined operation on complex numbers (there is no "preferred choice" for the n-th root in general, and you have n different options to choose from generally), and requiring a bunch of choices. After those, it\'s still not a continuous operation, so you\'ll have a sudden "jump" in the outcomes at some place. All in all, a rule like zab=(za)b simply cannot hold then anymore.
